The paper deals with extremal graph theory, which is a subfield of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). It also involves the study of directed graphs and paths, which are topics in both computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and graph theory (cs.GT).
